1
00:00:04,180 --> 00:00:07,900
Thank you, Gwen. It was beautiful, as always.

2
00:00:11,540 --> 00:00:21,300
Communion really grabs me this day, as I'm on the eve, or the day after, rather, of celebrating the birthday of my oldest son.

3
00:00:22,370 --> 00:00:28,330
His birthday is actually next week, but the crazy party was yesterday. I survived it.

4
00:00:28,330 --> 00:00:35,270
But it's a poignant time as well when you think about a son, or a child, a daughter,

5
00:00:35,270 --> 00:00:42,570
and what it means that the father would give that child up for others.

6
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:55,750
We had a good time bowling, if you can imagine, 13 kids dropping heavy balls everywhere

7
00:00:55,750 --> 00:01:00,030
and running on those little shoes that slide.

8
00:01:01,040 --> 00:01:03,140
It was a day I will never forget.

9
00:01:03,140 --> 00:01:10,820
We had a great time, but still the idea of God giving up his son really captures me.

10
00:01:12,020 --> 00:01:14,600
And because he did that, we can pray.

11
00:01:15,260 --> 00:01:18,040
We can come into the presence of the Father.

12
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:20,840
And I'm so amazed by that.

13
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:26,820
And so we continue our second of three weeks in this issue of prayer before we get underway in the fall season.

14
00:01:28,180 --> 00:01:32,260
And so number two, we're talking about some principles this morning for answered prayer.

15
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:36,210
We start talking about prayer.

16
00:01:36,610 --> 00:01:40,710
We get to the issue of answered prayer.

17
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:46,980
because in the Christian worldview, this is not a gimmick or an exercise

18
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:52,360
or some kind of technique to relax your muscles.

19
00:01:53,100 --> 00:02:00,420
This is not an Eastern philosophical experience of emptying yourself into the great nothingness.

20
00:02:00,420 --> 00:02:07,880
Prayer in the Christian context is talking to God person to person.

21
00:02:08,930 --> 00:02:17,120
It's a whole different kind of experience than is offered today in the culture of our day

22
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:25,440
where prayer is a meditation, a technique, something you learn at the local yoga or health club.

23
00:02:26,490 --> 00:02:30,190
Friends, prayer is something far deeper than those experiences.

24
00:02:30,410 --> 00:02:32,910
Prayer is a dynamic between persons.

25
00:02:32,910 --> 00:02:43,630
prayer is part of a relationship between god and human beings prayer is conversing and listening

26
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:54,800
to the king of kings and there's nothing like it in all the world amen i agree and when you

27
00:02:54,800 --> 00:03:02,500
converse and listen to another person there is the expectation that you will connect and receive

28
00:03:02,500 --> 00:03:08,940
results, that there will be an answer to the discussion. The same is true in prayer with our

29
00:03:08,940 --> 00:03:15,930
Heavenly Father. And like in any relationship where there's tension, there's strife or problems

30
00:03:15,930 --> 00:03:22,390
between those two persons, the communication can be strained and the results can be shaky at best.

31
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:29,640
And the same can happen in prayer as well. And we'll explore that this morning. And so that we

32
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:36,200
might be effective in prayer. I'm going to share what the Bible says in various places

33
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:41,340
about four principles that I came up with out of Scripture for answered prayer. And

34
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:48,440
my hope is that this will be helpful. You'll find it effective. And so the first one may

35
00:03:48,440 --> 00:03:56,440
sound basic, but it's the foundation. And we all need to be reminded again that number

36
00:03:56,440 --> 00:04:04,560
one, for effective prayer, we must have an honest relationship to God. And the key there

37
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:12,020
is an honest relationship with God. I want to come back to a text that we saw last week

38
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:21,330
in John chapter 15. Jesus said to the disciples, but if you stay joined to me and my words

39
00:04:21,330 --> 00:04:29,260
remain in you. You may ask any request you like, and it will be granted. That's a wonderful,

40
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:36,560
amazing promise. But I would like for us to look a little more closely, because there's a promise

41
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:44,980
there, but there's also a premise underneath. And the premise is that we have to stay joined to

42
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:53,950
Jesus Christ, that we are to remain in him, that his words are to remain in us. And so the question

43
00:04:53,950 --> 00:05:03,340
becomes, how do we stay joined to Jesus Christ and let his words remain in us? We have to have an

44
00:05:03,340 --> 00:05:12,920
honest relationship with God, an honest relationship. We have to talk to Jesus. We have to let his words

45
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:15,900
permeate our minds and our hearts.

46
00:05:16,620 --> 00:05:20,360
We have to live out his words in actions.

47
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,520
And we put those words into our souls

48
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:27,080
by reading and memorizing and learning

49
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:29,000
and studying the scriptures.

50
00:05:30,290 --> 00:05:33,790
We have to have an honest relationship with God.

51
00:05:35,940 --> 00:05:38,280
How do we know if we're having

52
00:05:38,280 --> 00:05:39,820
an honest relationship with God?

53
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:41,200
I've got three things to share.

54
00:05:42,830 --> 00:05:45,390
And the book of 1 John begins to help us

55
00:05:45,390 --> 00:05:52,420
understand if our relationship with God is real and true and honest. And so the first question we

56
00:05:52,420 --> 00:06:02,500
can ask ourselves is this, am I refusing to admit wrongs I have done in the past? The Bible has a

57
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:10,510
word for that, calls it unconfessed sin. These might be attitudes, they might be actions, addictions

58
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:18,660
or habits, whatever it is that is holding us back from drawing close unto God, when

59
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:23,450
we take part of those activities, it displeases God.

60
00:06:24,010 --> 00:06:25,390
It breaks our connection with Him.

61
00:06:25,870 --> 00:06:32,210
But the good news is this, and out of 1 John 1, verse 8 and following, he says,

62
00:06:32,210 --> 00:06:39,790
If we say we have no sin, we're only fooling ourselves and refusing to accept the truth.

63
00:06:39,790 --> 00:06:50,050
but if we confess our sins to him he is faithful and just to forgive us and to cleanse us from

64
00:06:50,050 --> 00:06:58,030
every wrong if we claim we have not sinned we're calling god a liar and showing that his word

65
00:06:58,030 --> 00:07:07,210
has no place in our hearts so what is confession confession is simply being honest with god

66
00:07:07,710 --> 00:07:09,630
It's saying, God, you're right.

67
00:07:10,480 --> 00:07:11,280
I was wrong.

68
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:19,440
That attitude or that action, that jealousy, that impatience, whatever it is, was wrong.

69
00:07:20,300 --> 00:07:21,680
And God, I need your forgiveness.

70
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:31,640
You know you have an honest relationship with God when you're sensitive to the Holy Spirit speaking and convicting in your heart.

71
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:35,120
And instead of fighting back, you say, God, you're right.

72
00:07:36,450 --> 00:07:37,190
I was wrong.

73
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:39,040
That was a mistake.

74
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:41,840
I acknowledge that.

75
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:42,920
I confess that.

76
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,400
It's out in the open.

77
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:45,860
It's not hidden away.

78
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,200
It's out there.

79
00:07:50,090 --> 00:07:51,030
Now please take it away.

80
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:58,780
The second thing is, am I currently ignoring any of God's principles?

81
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:06,460
Are you consciously ignoring something that you know that God wants you to do?

82
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:12,960
Something that scripture is plain to you about, but you are conveniently ignoring those passages.

83
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:27,450
You might be conveniently ignoring that sense of disturbance in your conscience when you know what's the right thing and you begin to dally with doing the opposite.

84
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:36,880
The text in 1 John says this, this is the message he has given us to announce to you.

85
00:08:37,770 --> 00:08:41,290
God is light and there's no darkness in him at all.

86
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:49,520
So we are lying if we say we have fellowship with God, but go on living in spiritual darkness.

87
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,060
We're not living in the truth.

88
00:08:54,590 --> 00:08:59,230
But if we're living in the light of God's presence, just as Christ is,

89
00:08:59,690 --> 00:09:07,130
then we have fellowship with each other, and the blood of Jesus, His Son, it cleanses us from every sin.

90
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:18,610
I think the bottom line out of a text like this is you can't expect God to answer prayer when you're disobedient in a relationship with Him.

91
00:09:20,250 --> 00:09:28,110
If you're walking in darkness and ignoring God's principles for living right now, you're not in an honest relationship with God.

92
00:09:30,300 --> 00:09:38,200
God answers prayer when we get honest with Him and confess our sin and get real with God.

93
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:56,340
Number two, if we're going to have God answer our prayers, we're going to have to take on the forgiving attitude towards others.

94
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:03,220
If you're going to have answer to prayer, you're going to approach God with a forgiving attitude towards others.

95
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:12,130
I don't know if you've ever experienced this, but sometimes I pray in the quiet of my office or at home,

96
00:10:12,130 --> 00:10:18,890
And I just get this amazing sense that every prayer is doing this, boing, right off the ceiling.

97
00:10:20,040 --> 00:10:22,140
I'm just not getting through.

98
00:10:22,900 --> 00:10:26,500
And it's almost like it's bouncing around in the office or the home.

99
00:10:26,740 --> 00:10:30,640
And I can't figure out what's happening until God begins to say,

100
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:35,560
because you're angry with this person, or you're holding a grudge,

101
00:10:35,720 --> 00:10:38,740
or there's some issue you're holding towards others.

102
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:43,400
And it blocks my connection with my God.

103
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:47,680
Matthew 6.12, in Jesus, the Lord's Prayer,

104
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:51,040
he said, and forgive us our sins

105
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:55,380
just as we have forgiven those who sinned against us.

106
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:02,880
Oh, there's a connection, isn't there?

107
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:03,920
Yes.

108
00:11:05,900 --> 00:11:07,400
Earlier in the Sermon on the Mount,

109
00:11:07,520 --> 00:11:08,940
Jesus talked about reconciliation,

110
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:10,960
and he said in Matthew 5.23,

111
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:14,700
if you're standing before the altar in the temple

112
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:17,160
offering a sacrifice to God,

113
00:11:17,660 --> 00:11:19,240
and you suddenly remember

114
00:11:19,240 --> 00:11:21,220
that someone has something against you,

115
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:24,920
Leave your sacrifice beside the altar.

116
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:28,640
Go and be reconciled to that person.

117
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:33,390
Then come and offer the sacrifice to God.

118
00:11:36,260 --> 00:11:38,880
Why does he talk about reconciliation and forgiveness?

119
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:46,560
Because reconciliation and forgiveness are intimately related to our relationship with God.

120
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:50,400
And if we're going to experience dynamic answers in prayer,

121
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:55,760
we need our hearts to be clean from bitterness and resentment and unforgiveness.

122
00:11:57,210 --> 00:12:00,030
I love what Hebrews chapter 12 verse 15 says.

123
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:00,990
It captures it all.

124
00:12:02,450 --> 00:12:03,150
The writer says,

125
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:07,390
See to it that no one fails to obtain the grace of God,

126
00:12:08,340 --> 00:12:13,460
that no root of bitterness springs up and causes trouble,

127
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,660
and through it many become defiled.

128
00:12:17,860 --> 00:12:19,160
It's a powerful verse.

129
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:21,260
the root of bitterness

130
00:12:21,260 --> 00:12:23,980
that it not spring up

131
00:12:23,980 --> 00:12:25,200
and cause trouble

132
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:28,570
friends in my experience in my own life

133
00:12:28,570 --> 00:12:29,950
and in watching other people

134
00:12:29,950 --> 00:12:31,430
I have to say that bitterness

135
00:12:31,430 --> 00:12:34,310
will decimate your body

136
00:12:34,310 --> 00:12:36,220
that bitterness

137
00:12:36,220 --> 00:12:38,180
will literally shrivel

138
00:12:38,180 --> 00:12:39,240
your soul

139
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:42,100
that bitterness will cripple

140
00:12:42,100 --> 00:12:43,460
your life with God

141
00:12:43,460 --> 00:12:48,750
I had the privilege of having lunch

142
00:12:48,750 --> 00:12:50,230
breakfast rather this week

143
00:12:50,230 --> 00:12:54,550
with Dr. Earl Hensland, a new friend and colleague, a psychologist in the area.

144
00:12:55,510 --> 00:13:00,610
And he and I are working diligently on putting together this conference this fall in October,

145
00:13:00,610 --> 00:13:05,310
beginning about the middle of October on Tuesday nights, on spirituality and sexuality.

146
00:13:06,450 --> 00:13:07,770
We have two reasons for that.

147
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:10,790
One, it's an issue that the world is just buzzing about,

148
00:13:11,390 --> 00:13:13,630
but I think it's an issue for the church as well.

149
00:13:14,010 --> 00:13:18,110
And we're going to be dealing with all kinds of issues about wellness and passionate spirituality

150
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:22,230
as it relates to our bodies and our sexuality and how they all intertwine.

151
00:13:22,310 --> 00:13:24,290
It's going to be a fascinating three evenings.

152
00:13:24,990 --> 00:13:29,270
Dr. Amin from Newport Beach, a psychiatrist,

153
00:13:30,330 --> 00:13:34,130
one who's working on brain chemistry and all kinds of exciting things there,

154
00:13:34,630 --> 00:13:35,550
is going to be helping us.

155
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:37,670
It's going to be a fascinating evening.

156
00:13:37,670 --> 00:13:42,310
And as Earl and I talked this week about that conference and planning it,

157
00:13:42,310 --> 00:13:50,510
We began to talk also about how bitterness literally affects the mind and the brain and the soul.

158
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:56,030
And literally, when I say cripples and shrivels, I guess I'm not kidding.

159
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:59,230
He said, yes, it really does.

160
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:02,490
And some of those issues will come out in our conference.

161
00:14:04,090 --> 00:14:08,650
Bitterness and unforgiveness is a cancer to our bodies and to our souls.

162
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:13,210
And friends, you know people who have bitterness and unforgiveness in their lives.

163
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,340
And you know that they're miserable.

164
00:14:17,800 --> 00:14:18,640
And it could be you.

165
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,140
You might know them because you're pointing back.

166
00:14:21,620 --> 00:14:28,660
It's time for you and or for your friends and family to confess that bitterness and that anger and unforgiveness

167
00:14:28,660 --> 00:14:30,400
and let God take it away.

168
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:35,580
And when that experience happens, you get honest with God.

169
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:40,400
and you find the channel between you and the Heavenly Father opens up,

170
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:45,200
an effectual prayer begins to take place again in your life.

171
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:51,900
So the first principle in answering prayer, an effectual, honest prayer,

172
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:53,900
is an honest relationship with God.

173
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:58,200
And number two, it's a forgiving attitude towards others.

174
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:09,750
Third, I see Scripture affirming that we must, as human beings, have a generous spirit.

175
00:15:10,590 --> 00:15:11,550
A generous spirit.

176
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:20,060
As you search the scriptures, you'll see over and over that God is a God of love and mercy and generosity.

177
00:15:21,160 --> 00:15:24,800
That his heart is big in giving to others.

178
00:15:26,150 --> 00:15:27,830
It's in his heart to give.

179
00:15:27,830 --> 00:15:33,290
After all, as we symbolized here, he gave his only son for us.

180
00:15:35,380 --> 00:15:37,000
And God wants us to be like him.

181
00:15:37,900 --> 00:15:40,360
God wants us to take on his character.

182
00:15:41,770 --> 00:15:44,050
And if he wants our character to reflect his character,

183
00:15:44,330 --> 00:15:48,390
we're going to have to yearn for the things that God's heart yearns for.

184
00:15:48,390 --> 00:15:53,190
And God's heart yearns to be and continues to be a God who gives.

185
00:15:57,080 --> 00:16:02,270
The Bible affirms the spiritual principle that you will sow what you reap.

186
00:16:02,610 --> 00:16:04,430
What you give out comes back.

187
00:16:07,460 --> 00:16:10,280
I think it's not too much to say that if you want God to bless your life,

188
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:12,640
you're going to have to be willing to be a blessing to others.

189
00:16:13,640 --> 00:16:17,580
If you want the Lord to give to you, you must be willing to spread it around.

190
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:22,080
God is not interested in blessing that we might just get more and more,

191
00:16:22,360 --> 00:16:25,440
but that we might be a channel to bless others.

192
00:16:26,450 --> 00:16:28,830
Do you recall the phrase we talked about last year?

193
00:16:29,170 --> 00:16:32,960
God wants us to be a river and not a reservoir.

194
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:39,400
He wants to be a river that pours and flows and gives to others

195
00:16:39,400 --> 00:16:41,760
instead of holding as a reservoir.

196
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:46,210
Some of you are sitting out there very astute saying,

197
00:16:46,370 --> 00:16:48,150
hey, this is stewardship, not prayer.

198
00:16:49,550 --> 00:16:51,530
That's the November sermon series.

199
00:16:53,270 --> 00:16:53,950
But guess what?

200
00:16:54,860 --> 00:16:56,180
It's all stewardship.

201
00:16:57,130 --> 00:17:00,690
Because life is managing what God has given us.

202
00:17:01,310 --> 00:17:04,210
And it affects our life in prayer as well.

203
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:06,110
They're all interrelated.

204
00:17:06,810 --> 00:17:09,190
If you want God to meet your needs, friends,

205
00:17:09,190 --> 00:17:12,110
we must be willing to meet the needs of others.

206
00:17:13,370 --> 00:17:15,710
If you want God to bless you with a special treat,

207
00:17:16,010 --> 00:17:19,090
you must be willing to share that blessing with others.

208
00:17:20,940 --> 00:17:24,020
If you want God to bless you with a new attitude in your heart,

209
00:17:24,980 --> 00:17:28,840
God wants to see that attitude displayed in action toward others.

210
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:32,840
Proverbs 21, 13 says this,

211
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:36,910
If a man shuts his ears to the cry of the poor,

212
00:17:37,700 --> 00:17:41,440
he too will cry out and not be answered.

213
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,900
It's a strong principle about being a blessing to others.

214
00:17:46,420 --> 00:17:49,120
And it also has something to say about God's heart for the poor.

215
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:57,060
Look at 1 John chapter 3, verse 21 to 23.

216
00:17:57,360 --> 00:18:05,420
Dear friends, if our conscience is clear, we can come to God with bold confidence.

217
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:13,470
And we will receive whatever request because we obey him and do the things that please him.

218
00:18:14,170 --> 00:18:15,850
And this is his commandment.

219
00:18:15,850 --> 00:18:23,810
We must believe in the name of his son, Jesus Christ, and love one another just as he commanded us.

220
00:18:25,630 --> 00:18:29,410
So to receive from God, we're going to have to follow his commands.

221
00:18:29,690 --> 00:18:34,770
And his commands here are believing in Jesus Christ and loving one another.

222
00:18:37,710 --> 00:18:38,410
Loving one another.

223
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:41,300
That's being a blessing to other people.

224
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:46,500
Look at verses 16 and 18 of that same text.

225
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:48,760
1 John chapter 3.

226
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:54,420
We know what real love is because Christ gave up his life for us.

227
00:18:55,540 --> 00:19:00,100
And so we also ought to give up our lives for our Christian brothers and sisters.

228
00:19:01,290 --> 00:19:06,330
But if anyone has enough money to live well and sees a brother or sister in need

229
00:19:06,330 --> 00:19:11,660
and refuses to help, how can God's love be in that person?

230
00:19:13,150 --> 00:19:17,310
Dear children, let us stop just saying we love each other.

231
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:20,990
Let us really show it by our actions.

232
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,660
Do you see what the Bible is saying there?

233
00:19:24,060 --> 00:19:26,860
Do you see how it's saying that love is practical?

234
00:19:27,220 --> 00:19:28,860
That love is action?

235
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:31,370
It's more than a warm fuzzy.

236
00:19:31,370 --> 00:19:37,310
It expresses itself in tangible, concrete ways in the lives of others.

237
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:42,920
And God blesses us so that we might bless other people

238
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:45,620
and be a channel of blessing in the world.

239
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:47,560
That's that principle of stewardship.

240
00:19:47,980 --> 00:19:51,960
And it's all throughout the Scripture that God blesses

241
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,780
in order that we might be a blessing to others.

242
00:19:56,960 --> 00:20:00,560
Answered prayer comes from an honest relationship with God.

243
00:20:02,190 --> 00:20:04,630
It comes from a forgiving attitude towards others.

244
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:11,040
And it comes as God gives us a generous spirit.

245
00:20:12,280 --> 00:20:18,280
And finally, number four, I've put down that we must pray in Jesus' name.

246
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:21,470
Pray in Jesus' name.

247
00:20:22,380 --> 00:20:22,980
What does that mean?

248
00:20:24,460 --> 00:20:28,560
We tack on the phrase, in Jesus' name, at the end of our prayers,

249
00:20:29,060 --> 00:20:32,880
but I'm not always sure that we always know really what that means.

250
00:20:34,780 --> 00:20:36,420
The Scriptures give this idea.

251
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:39,100
If you read it in a straightforward manner, listen to this.

252
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:42,020
John 14, verse 13.

253
00:20:43,250 --> 00:20:43,870
Jesus says,

254
00:20:43,870 --> 00:20:48,070
You can ask for anything in my name, and I will do it,

255
00:20:48,550 --> 00:20:52,330
because the work of the Son brings glory to the Father.

256
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:57,200
Yes, ask anything in my name, and I will do it.

257
00:21:00,510 --> 00:21:05,990
But Jesus is saying more than just putting a phrase to a prayer to make it effective.

258
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:10,980
Is that always asking that we just, if I throw on in Jesus' name,

259
00:21:11,060 --> 00:21:15,160
it's sort of a magic incantation that somehow opens up the keys to heaven?

260
00:21:15,340 --> 00:21:16,320
I don't think so.

261
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:24,980
To pray in Jesus' name is to recognize the authority by which you are coming to God.

262
00:21:24,980 --> 00:21:30,030
You are approaching the God of the universe when you come in prayer.

263
00:21:30,530 --> 00:21:32,070
And it's not to be taken lightly.

264
00:21:32,870 --> 00:21:34,090
But you are welcome.

265
00:21:35,180 --> 00:21:35,840
Catch this.

266
00:21:36,140 --> 00:21:41,440
You are welcome to come because of what Jesus Christ did on the cross.

267
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:46,060
You are welcome to come because of what he did on the cross.

268
00:21:47,170 --> 00:21:48,750
Hebrews chapter 10 verse 21.

269
00:21:48,750 --> 00:21:54,390
And since we have a great high priest who rules over God's people,

270
00:21:54,390 --> 00:22:01,190
Let us go right into the presence of God with true hearts, fully trusting him.

271
00:22:03,350 --> 00:22:04,130
Did you catch that?

272
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:09,070
Let us come right into the presence of God.

273
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:15,460
For our evil consciences have been sprinkled with Christ's blood to make us clean,

274
00:22:16,040 --> 00:22:19,840
and our bodies have been washed with pure water.

275
00:22:22,690 --> 00:22:25,870
We're approaching God, friends, because of what Jesus did on the cross

276
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:29,170
and taking our guilt and our shame upon himself

277
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:32,050
and thereby removing it from us.

278
00:22:32,470 --> 00:22:35,950
Therefore, the channel between God and human beings is open

279
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:40,150
and we do that because Jesus has given us the right

280
00:22:40,150 --> 00:22:42,610
to do it as the Son of God.

281
00:22:43,750 --> 00:22:47,120
We come to God in the authority of Jesus.

282
00:22:50,780 --> 00:22:54,570
I read a story that I think illustrates this issue.

283
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:59,140
A pastor took his young son and 14 of his friends to a carnival

284
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:02,700
And I can relate to that, having just been at one myself in some ways.

285
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:10,240
And so here they are at this carnival, and the father buys a whole roll of tickets.

286
00:23:10,360 --> 00:23:12,200
You know what I'm talking about, the big red tickets.

287
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:18,120
And at each ride, the 14 kids would line up, and he would start doling out the tickets.

288
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:23,660
And each, one by one, the children came by and snatched the tickets and headed on to the attraction.

289
00:23:24,620 --> 00:23:28,440
And three or four rides into the experience, father's just doling out the tickets.

290
00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:39,270
he looks up and sees a kid he doesn't recognize and as the story goes the father asked and said

291
00:23:39,270 --> 00:23:48,140
son are you with this party and the kid said no and he said well why should i give you a ticket

292
00:23:48,140 --> 00:23:55,320
and the young boy turned around this is so deep the young boy turns and points to the man's son

293
00:23:55,320 --> 00:24:04,830
and says he said you'd give me a ticket and so he did and if you see the spiritual connection

294
00:24:04,830 --> 00:24:12,780
the father's son is like Jesus giving authority that the father might give out, that they might

295
00:24:12,780 --> 00:24:19,340
come and receive from the father. That child gave the authority that this little child might come

296
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:27,970
and receive from that father. I love that image. It's touching, but it's real, isn't it? Because

297
00:24:27,970 --> 00:24:33,950
that's in a sense what Jesus has done in his authority, gives us the opportunity and the

298
00:24:33,950 --> 00:24:42,270
privilege of coming right into the throne room of God. And God gives, and we might receive.

299
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:51,180
When you're truly praying, friends, in Jesus' name, you're cognizant of the costliness

300
00:24:51,180 --> 00:25:01,640
of prayer. You realize what it costs Jesus to have you come before God. And from that position,

301
00:25:01,640 --> 00:25:06,580
you come desiring that your prayers are lining up with what God is doing

302
00:25:06,580 --> 00:25:09,280
and his intention for your life.

303
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,420
You see, prayer is not something to be trifled with.

304
00:25:12,720 --> 00:25:15,180
Prayer is powerful, and prayer changes things.

305
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:18,760
And most notably, it will change the one who is praying.

306
00:25:19,520 --> 00:25:22,360
So look out, friends, because as you come into the throne room,

307
00:25:22,520 --> 00:25:24,140
you will leave different.

308
00:25:25,500 --> 00:25:27,330
And that's good. That's good.

309
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:36,200
So, do you always tack on in Jesus' name at the end of every prayer?

310
00:25:37,750 --> 00:25:42,250
I don't think it's necessary to say it as if it's some little formula,

311
00:25:43,360 --> 00:25:46,760
but if you've got the right attitude, I think it's a good idea to remind you

312
00:25:46,760 --> 00:25:50,860
in what authority, in whose authority, do you come to the throne room.

313
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:55,220
You can put it on the front end.

314
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:59,290
Dear Father, I come in Jesus' name, by his authority,

315
00:26:00,190 --> 00:26:05,270
and thank you that my might ask of these things, and such and such.

316
00:26:06,120 --> 00:26:06,700
And then amen.

317
00:26:08,890 --> 00:26:11,150
See, amen is simply a word that says,

318
00:26:11,450 --> 00:26:13,090
Yes, so be it.

319
00:26:13,410 --> 00:26:14,630
That's what I want.

320
00:26:14,990 --> 00:26:16,170
That's what's happening.

321
00:26:17,450 --> 00:26:18,690
Amen, it says in Greek.

322
00:26:18,830 --> 00:26:19,170
Yes.

323
00:26:25,140 --> 00:26:27,760
I think it's a good idea that we might say it over and over, though,

324
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:30,780
to remind us in whose authority we come.

325
00:26:32,380 --> 00:26:33,560
In Jesus' authority.

326
00:26:35,300 --> 00:26:37,780
And so, friends, I wrap this up by saying this,

327
00:26:37,780 --> 00:26:42,700
that effectual prayer comes from an honest relationship with God.

328
00:26:43,930 --> 00:26:46,050
And you might ask yourself, am I being honest with God?

329
00:26:46,230 --> 00:26:47,350
Do I really know God?

330
00:26:48,650 --> 00:26:49,730
Do I really know God?

331
00:26:50,050 --> 00:26:52,330
Do I know Jesus and am I walking with Him

332
00:26:52,330 --> 00:26:54,590
that I might come into the throne room of God

333
00:26:54,590 --> 00:26:57,230
and honestly connect with the Heavenly Father?

334
00:26:57,310 --> 00:26:58,550
That's an honest relationship.

335
00:27:00,010 --> 00:27:01,950
Do you honestly desire the things of Scripture

336
00:27:01,950 --> 00:27:03,950
to be what your heart is all about?

337
00:27:05,050 --> 00:27:06,670
That's an honest relationship with God.

338
00:27:07,370 --> 00:27:08,850
Number two is a forgiving spirit,

339
00:27:08,990 --> 00:27:10,570
a forgiving attitude towards others.

340
00:27:11,750 --> 00:27:13,490
Are you asking God to bless you

341
00:27:13,490 --> 00:27:15,670
and yet you are just full of bitterness

342
00:27:15,670 --> 00:27:17,310
and rage towards somebody else?

343
00:27:17,410 --> 00:27:18,590
Friends, it doesn't work that way.

344
00:27:19,010 --> 00:27:23,190
God blesses a clean heart.

345
00:27:24,770 --> 00:27:27,290
And if we're holding on to unforgiveness and bitterness,

346
00:27:28,500 --> 00:27:31,540
it must be confessed and let go of.

347
00:27:34,990 --> 00:27:36,190
Do you have a selfish heart?

348
00:27:36,850 --> 00:27:38,910
Because God wants us to have a generous heart.

349
00:27:39,540 --> 00:27:43,160
One that gives to others as God gives to us.

350
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:48,560
And finally, we pray by the authority that Jesus gives us

351
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:51,560
in his name, in his authority.

352
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,320
Prayer, my friends and family,

353
00:27:55,380 --> 00:27:57,660
is an incredible privilege of a Christian.

354
00:27:58,580 --> 00:28:00,900
It's the lifeblood of our spiritual life.

355
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:04,320
It's the channel for God's blessing in this world.

356
00:28:04,820 --> 00:28:06,860
And I just want to ask this last question.

357
00:28:06,860 --> 00:28:09,760
Are you ready for that kind of adventure?

358
00:28:10,500 --> 00:28:14,000
Are you ready to truly take off on that adventure

359
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:15,920
and to learn to pray?

360
00:28:16,120 --> 00:28:17,740
As Jesus said, I conclude,

361
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:20,540
Lord, teach us to pray.

362
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:23,420
Lord, teach us to pray.

363
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,080
Let's pray.

364
00:28:26,220 --> 00:28:31,020
Lord, our Father, teach us to pray.

365
00:28:33,340 --> 00:28:39,060
Lord, teach us to pray what it means to pray in Jesus' name and by his authority.

366
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:42,980
Lord, teach us to pray with generous hearts.

367
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:53,280
Lord, teach us to pray with an attitude of humility and forgiveness towards others.

368
00:28:54,910 --> 00:29:00,410
Lord, teach us to pray in an honest relationship with you.

369
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:05,960
Father, I pray that your spirit would come this morning

370
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:11,850
and manifest itself in moving in our lives

371
00:29:11,850 --> 00:29:14,930
and going deep into each person.

372
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,820
And if need be, to prick our conscience

373
00:29:19,820 --> 00:29:22,740
and to make us aware of where we need to change,

374
00:29:23,220 --> 00:29:25,700
that these issues that we've looked at

375
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:27,600
might become reality for us.

376
00:29:29,650 --> 00:29:34,220
So Holy Spirit, I pray that you will move amongst us,

377
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:39,590
including me, and show us how to get on the right track,

378
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:42,510
what attitudes need to be exhibited,

379
00:29:42,730 --> 00:29:46,630
how we are to fall in line with what you're doing in our lives.

380
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:49,480
So have your way, Lord, with us.

381
00:29:50,570 --> 00:29:53,350
Thank you, Jesus, for the incredible privilege

382
00:29:53,350 --> 00:29:56,010
of coming into the throne room of grace.

383
00:29:58,220 --> 00:30:00,120
And thank you for the incredible sacrifice

384
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:03,240
that you enacted on our behalf.

385
00:30:04,660 --> 00:30:08,480
And Father, thank you for creating us,

386
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:11,620
for giving us so much,

387
00:30:12,680 --> 00:30:14,800
and providing access to you,

388
00:30:16,340 --> 00:30:18,920
that we're not lost, that we're not separate from you,

389
00:30:18,980 --> 00:30:21,940
but that we are able to come and to say Abba,

390
00:30:21,940 --> 00:30:25,140
to say Daddy, to the King of the Universe.

391
00:30:26,010 --> 00:30:26,690
Thank you.

392
00:30:28,810 --> 00:30:31,490
Now may these truths become real in our lives,

393
00:30:32,660 --> 00:30:36,300
and may Fullerton First Baptist continue to be a praying church,

394
00:30:37,110 --> 00:30:38,890
a church that seeks you,

395
00:30:38,890 --> 00:30:41,770
a church that seeks your power

396
00:30:41,770 --> 00:30:43,170
and calls it down in prayer

397
00:30:43,170 --> 00:30:45,890
and a church that is seeking to be transformed

398
00:30:45,890 --> 00:30:48,090
by being in prayer with you

399
00:30:48,090 --> 00:30:50,500
so have your way

400
00:30:50,500 --> 00:30:54,330
and accomplish your purposes we pray

401
00:30:54,330 --> 00:30:56,290
in Jesus name

402
00:30:56,290 --> 00:30:58,150
by his authority we pray together

403
00:30:58,150 --> 00:31:00,830
amen and amen

